HEADWORD: Pelagic
<hw>Pe*lag"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pelagicus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the ocean; --
applied especially to animals that live at the surface of the ocean,
away from the coast. Compare <contr>benthic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelargonic</ent>⟦br⟧
